OL,6,FBritish Medical Association chair of
OL,7,Fcouncil Professor Philip Banfield
OL,8,Fsaid: "Corridor care should never ever
OL,9,Fbe 'the norm' in any hospital and yet,
OL,10,Fas this report reveals, our patients
OL,11,Fare being looked after, not in beds,
OL,12,Fon wards or in proper cubicles, but in
OL,13,Fplaces which are unsafe and inhumane.
OL,15,F"Doctors, and now our nursing
OL,16,Fcolleagues, are almost beyond despair
OL,17,Fas they struggle with the impossible
OL,18,Ftask of trying vainly to look after
OL,19,Fscores of sick and dying people, left
OL,20,Ffor hours on end in unsanitary and
OL,21,Funacceptable conditions."
