OL,6,F"Our nurses are as hard-working and
OL,7,Fcommitted as ever, but they cannot
OL,8,Fdefend the NHS against the SNP's
OL,9,Fmismanagement forever."
OL,11,FHealth Secretary Neil Gray said: "I
OL,12,Fwant to apologise to anyone whose
OL,13,Fexperience of the NHS has fallen short
OL,14,Fof the standards we all expect from
OL,15,Four health service.
OL,17,F"A&E departments are under pressure
OL,18,Fdue to high occupancy and delays with
OL,19,Fpatients who need extra support before
OL,20,Fgoing home, which affects the flow of
OL,21,Fpatients from A&E to inpatient wards.
